tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  19,81,"(And they have chosen (other)) the people of Mecca worshipped (gods beside Allah) i.e. idols (that they may be a power for them) that they be a protection for them from Allah's chastisement."
  19,84,"(So make no haste against them (O Muhammad)) do not hasten chastisement upon them. (We do but number unto them a sum) one breath after another."
  19,88,"(And they say) i.e. the Jews: (The Beneficent hath taken unto Himself a son) He has taken Ezra ('Uzayr) as his son."
  19,92,"(When it is not meet for (the Majesty of) the Beneficent that He should choose a son) It does not befit him to take Ezra as a son."
  19,94,"(Verily He knoweth them) He remembers them (and numbereth them with (right) numbering) and He knows their number."